Zoe there's an old school saying here in Australia regarding the sky and how it predicts the weather; Red sky at night, Sailor's delight. Red sky in the morning, Sailor's warning. Basically means a red sky at dusk will bring lovely weather the following day but if it's red in the morning it'll bring bad or rough weather. Mum taught me this when I was a kid because she had a job working outside, it stuck with me and is quite reliable!
